  <bioghist id="aspace_6800eb0a53e189b5a12e92115571108b">
    <head>Biographical Note</head>
<p>Irene Kahn born Irene Cohen, the daughter of Latvian immigrants. She used the name Irene Kahn as an adult and continued to use that name after her marriage to Samuel Berkman. Kahn, who joined the Hartt faculty in 1924, was a professor of piano, theory, and opera. She also taught at both St. Joseph's College and the University of Connecticut. She was remembered as the driving force behind many Hartt productions and within the University community. Kahn passed away in April 20, 1996, shortly after celebrarting her 92nd birthday.</p>  </bioghist>
  <processinfo id="aspace_f3191087f08dd775771f9b6acbc35ca7">
    <head>Processing Information</head>
<p>In 2015, the call number was changed from HM25 to ARCH071. Between 2015-2017, this collection was listed as "Irene Kahn Papers" and was changed back to the "Irene Kahn Collection" following the 2017 reprocessing.</p>  </processinfo>
  <processinfo audience="internal" id="aspace_45f5638befeb4af720030086ae9053ad">
    <head>Processing Information</head>
<p>Between 2015-2017, this collection was listed as "Irene Kahn Papers." During the inventory of the archives, in which collections were given their ARCH### ID numbers, the collection title was changed to "Papers" in an attempt to be more compliant with DACS, however during the 2017 reprocessing, a growing number of items appeared to have been merged from other collections including the Hartt Faculty Collection, by the archives in the past. The name was therefore, changed back to the "Irene Kahn Collection."</p>  </processinfo>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_45d3cd91260ab65783deb66a4bfe242c">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>The collection contains a variety of professional and personal items including correspondence, memorabilia, and photographs. Many of the photographs are of Kahn and her family members, particularly her husband and Hartt Professor Samuel Berkman, as well as of colleagues, students, and visiting performers. Many of the photographs have inscriptions and autographs.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <arrangement id="aspace_43f0742c3075f50bdbbe0140b97d879c">
    <head>Arrangement</head>
<p>The collection is arranged alphabetically by filename.</p>  </arrangement>
